Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
first, look around to see if there are traffic lights near you. find the nearest one, then walk there. next, see the color of the traffic light right opposite to you. if it is red, you should wait till the light changes to green. if it is green, look around to make sure that there are no cars coming to you, and then go across the street quickly.